    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''How Islam Won, and Lost, the Lead in Science'' (Oct. 30): The article calls attention to parallel impediments placed on Western science by our own religious fundamentalists. Since their initial suggestion that the destruction of the World Trade Center was an expression of the wrath of God, they have been relatively quiet.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''How Islam Won, and Lost, the Lead in Science'' (Oct. 30): The article calls attention to parallel impediments placed on Western science by our own religious fundamentalists. Since their initial suggestion that the destruction of the World Trade Center was an expression of the wrath of God, they have been relatively quiet.</p>
        <p>But their attitude has already spawned comparably destructive acts of piety, like the bombing of abortion clinics and minority churches, and opposition to the study of evolution and federal financing of cell research.</p>
        <p>Are we now witnessing the decline of Western science and the passing of the baton to Asia, where fewer limits are placed on creative thinking and its technological results? As we see, it's happened be fore.</p>
        <p>DR. BERTON C. PRESSMAN  Miami</p>
      </block>
